00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:39,773
Need to be in control of myself,
you know what I'm saying?

240
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:42,109
- Take command of your life.
- Something.

241
00:15:42,192 --> 00:15:45,403
- Cultivate some self-discipline.
- Or whatever.

242
00:15:45,487 --> 00:15:49,533
What if I told you
that there's a certain liberation,

243
00:15:49,825 --> 00:15:53,286
not in command or in self-control,
but in surrendering?

244
00:15:53,370 --> 00:15:55,997
Well, that depends
on who you surrendering to.

245
00:15:58,333 --> 00:16:00,460
Oh, that.

246
00:16:00,794 --> 00:16:04,214
All due respect, you can stow that patter
right here and now.

247
00:16:06,383 --> 00:16:10,220
Look, it ain't about me doing for me,
I don't think.

248
00:16:10,387 --> 00:16:12,556
Might need to be about more than that.

249
00:16:13,223 --> 00:16:16,935
So you're bringing in an overall decline
of 2% for the month

250
00:16:17,018 --> 00:16:21,982
but almost half of that's coming from
an 8% drop in the western district?

251
00:16:22,107 --> 00:16:25,527
Major Colvin is himself willing
to acknowledge the possibility

252
00:16:25,610 --> 00:16:28,905
of a statistical variation from the mean
in his monthly stats.

253
00:16:29,072 --> 00:16:31,199
Variation, huh?

254
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,911
If I look through the
western incident reports

255
00:16:34,995 --> 00:16:39,416
am I likely to find less crime or more incidents
which have been downgraded or unfounded?

256
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:43,128
Because this kind of variation
screams manipulation to me,

257
00:16:43,253 --> 00:16:46,047
and if I'm wrong,
if indeed there is no manipulation,

258
00:16:46,214 --> 00:16:48,508
what has major Colvin learned

259
00:16:48,592 --> 00:16:51,178
about police work that eludes
the rest of your commanders?

260
00:16:51,261 --> 00:16:54,931
Councilman, I assure you, these stats
are not massaged. We don't do that.

261
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:58,560
I don't do that.
And I won't allow my people to do that.

262
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:01,646
Our feeling is that
it's genuinely an aberration.

263
00:17:01,813 --> 00:17:06,568
And if it repeats itself next month, then
it bears closer examination. Othen/vise...

264
00:17:06,651 --> 00:17:09,863
Moving on, then.
How are we fixed for witness assistance?

265
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:12,949
Does the department have sufficient funds
to ensure security

266
00:17:13,116 --> 00:17:15,160
for any endangered witnesses?

267
00:17:16,953 --> 00:17:20,957
We have the resources
that the city can afford, I'm sure.

268
00:17:21,082 --> 00:17:23,126
I understand you can't criticize the mayor.

269
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:26,296
- Nor would I.
- Nor would you.

270
00:17:27,130 --> 00:17:28,798
So allow me to ask the question.

271
00:17:29,132 --> 00:17:31,092
What is this city willing to pay

272
00:17:31,218 --> 00:17:33,386
for ordinary people to come down
to the courthouse

273
00:17:33,470 --> 00:17:37,182
and perform the civic duty of bearing
witness against gangsters and criminals?

274
00:17:38,225 --> 00:17:41,102
What resources are commensurate
with that kind of commitment?

275
00:17:43,563 --> 00:17:46,858
You can play the good soldier if you want,
but I want to go on the record

276
00:17:46,983 --> 00:17:50,528
in saying that this administration
has passed the buck time and again

277
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:54,241
and failed to protect citizens
who demonstrate that kind of commitment

278
00:17:54,324 --> 00:17:57,244
and put their lives and livelihood at risk.

279
00:17:58,411 --> 00:18:01,122
I would like to add
that I feel as my colleague does.

280
00:18:01,206 --> 00:18:04,000
This administration
has failed this community.

281
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:07,212
Miserably. And we need
to do something about this.

282
00:18:13,176 --> 00:18:14,386
Come on.

283
00:18:14,803 --> 00:18:17,180
Hey! Hey, hey, hey!

284
00:18:17,514 --> 00:18:19,307
Take him, man, you got him.

285
00:18:19,975 --> 00:18:23,228
Y'all are friends. You're like brothers.

286
00:18:25,188 --> 00:18:28,692
You lose that, you lose every damn thing.
Go on.

287
00:18:34,572 --> 00:18:36,032
Kids messed up the good hoop.

288
00:18:36,241 --> 00:18:39,077
Now they got one
looks like the original peach basket...

289
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,079
And they hanging onto it like a tit.

290
00:18:42,372 --> 00:18:43,415
I don't know.

291
00:18:44,916 --> 00:18:47,627
Maybe I should get up
some kind of tournament.

292
00:18:47,711 --> 00:18:48,837
You play basketball?

293
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:53,091
Never was much for balls and sticks.
I was always about my hands.

294
00:18:53,174 --> 00:18:55,302
- Boxer?
- Yeah.

295
00:18:55,385 --> 00:18:56,928
Boxing?

296
00:18:57,887 --> 00:19:00,390
I know a place
where some of the kids go but...

297
00:19:00,932 --> 00:19:05,145
- It ain't near close enough to here.
- I wouldn't mind taking a look at it.

298
00:19:05,228 --> 00:19:07,355
Get a mental picture at least.

299
00:19:07,939 --> 00:19:09,733
What the hell's going on here?

300
00:19:11,318 --> 00:19:14,154
Police pushed all the action down here.

301
00:19:14,237 --> 00:19:16,132
The Deacon thinks maybe some people
should come in here

302
00:19:16,156 --> 00:19:18,491
and take over the situation.

303
00:19:18,575 --> 00:19:21,328
- Are you that people?
- One of them, maybe.

304
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:24,664
- Roman, man.
- Dennis.

305
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:41,681
You should lay back on this one. Let me go
talk to buford pusser in there alone.

306
00:19:41,765 --> 00:19:43,058
Excuse me?

307
00:19:44,642 --> 00:19:47,020
And what it shows people
is that I know my business.

308
00:19:47,103 --> 00:19:50,690
That I will hold people accountable
based on the facts.

309
00:19:50,899 --> 00:19:53,276
- It's about what's right.
- There you go again.

310
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:54,527
What?

311
00:19:54,611 --> 00:19:57,322
Do you think politics
is only about winning the argument?

312
00:19:57,405 --> 00:20:00,825
That whoever has the right fact
at the right moment wins?

313
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:05,038
Clinton had facts. Kennedy had facts.
Yeah, but Reagan?

314
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:07,374
He couldn't summon a fact to save his life.

315
00:20:07,582 --> 00:20:10,251
It's not just facts, it's how you use them.

316
00:20:10,335 --> 00:20:13,797
When you get hold of a fact you go
smart-ass and start beating on people.

317
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:15,715
- That's...
- Clinton and Reagan...

318
00:20:15,799 --> 00:20:17,133
When they got up to speak,

319
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:20,929
they gave everyone in the room
comfort and confidence.

320
00:20:21,012 --> 00:20:25,392
You liked those guys. You were happy
to think that they even liked you.

321
00:20:25,683 --> 00:20:27,811
You're saying I'm not likable?

322
00:20:29,104 --> 00:20:30,480
Jen?

323
00:20:31,481 --> 00:20:33,733
When you're at home talking with me,

324
00:20:33,817 --> 00:20:38,530
not the council, not the cameras,
you're great.

325
00:20:38,655 --> 00:20:42,951
When you tell me
what's really important to you, I believe.

326
00:20:43,076 --> 00:20:47,539
You're smart, and you're ambitious,
and you've got a sharper tongue than most.

327
00:20:47,664 --> 00:20:49,916
You can hold court, tell a good story,

328
00:20:49,999 --> 00:20:52,502
and you can win the argument if you want.

329
00:20:53,002 --> 00:20:54,754
All of that shows, Tommy.

330
00:20:54,963 --> 00:20:57,674
And at a city council
meeting, it shows well.

331
00:20:57,757 --> 00:21:02,804
But if you want to be mayor,
or senator, or governor one day...

332
00:21:03,012 --> 00:21:05,014
Show 'em something more.

333
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:09,936
Baltimore?

334
00:21:10,186 --> 00:21:13,398
Went up there to the harbor
with my wife for our anniversary.

335
00:21:13,481 --> 00:21:18,027
- Charged us $12 for two beers.
- Shit, that's the least of it.

336
00:21:18,528 --> 00:21:21,281
The whole damn town's
going to hell in a handbasket.

337
00:21:21,573 --> 00:21:24,200
- And guess who's running the show?
- Who?

338
00:21:24,492 --> 00:21:28,872
Who do you think?
The department, city hall, the courts.

339
00:21:28,955 --> 00:21:30,123
Shit, the courts?

340
00:21:30,373 --> 00:21:34,669
You know what they call it when judge, jury
and perp all go to the same family barbecue?

341
00:21:35,211 --> 00:21:38,131
- Catch and release.
- No shit.

342
00:21:38,214 --> 00:21:40,800
God have mercy on any poor white boy
going to trial.

343
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:43,887
Then everybody's got their ass in the air
talking aboutjustice.

344
00:21:44,053 --> 00:21:46,389
Can't wait to throw away the key.

345
00:21:50,393 --> 00:21:53,563
I mean, they're not all so bad.

346
00:21:54,564 --> 00:21:56,858
Actually, there's a lot of good ones.

347
00:21:58,526 --> 00:22:00,862
I'm on the radio if you need me.

348
00:22:04,699 --> 00:22:06,868
My wife, Carol-Ann.

349
00:22:08,536 --> 00:22:11,164
- Some very good ones.
- Is there anything specific

350
00:22:11,247 --> 00:22:13,458
I can help you with while you're down here?

351
00:22:13,625 --> 00:22:16,252
Or is this just a courtesy call?

352
00:22:16,419 --> 00:22:20,173
You know, you should meet my partner.
You'd like her.

353
00:22:20,381 --> 00:22:22,467
Can't go through the front on this boy.

354
00:22:22,592 --> 00:22:25,470
So I'm thinking we're gonna have
to creep around the back.

355
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:27,639
Get devonne on it.

356
00:22:27,722 --> 00:22:30,892
Oh, I got this for that other problem.

357
00:22:34,979 --> 00:22:37,273
- Who this?
- Remember fatface Rick, right?

358
00:22:37,524 --> 00:22:40,443
Been going to meetings with string.
That's his cousin, trina.

359
00:22:40,527 --> 00:22:43,696
- You mean trina with the big old ass.
- Yeah, you on it.

360
00:22:43,947 --> 00:22:47,200
That's her work number.
You know where she working at nowadays?

361
00:22:47,325 --> 00:22:49,953
She over at the department
of social services.

362
00:22:50,203 --> 00:22:52,038
So you think Omar getting a check?

363
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:54,374
No, not now. But, I mean, once upon a time

364
00:22:54,457 --> 00:22:57,877
before some fool gave
little Omar little a shotgun,

365
00:22:57,961 --> 00:23:00,463
cocksucker was somebody's child, right?

366
00:23:00,838 --> 00:23:02,590
So somewhere down in them records

367
00:23:02,674 --> 00:23:05,802
is one or two names of Omar's people,
you feel me?

368
00:23:06,094 --> 00:23:09,138
You sure you want us
on marlo and Omar both?

369
00:23:09,222 --> 00:23:12,725
I mean, Omar ain't come back on us
since we got his bitch.

370
00:23:12,809 --> 00:23:16,020
- So maybe...
- Look, I'm home, Charles. I'm home.

371
00:23:18,356 --> 00:23:21,484
- What's up?
- Taking care of business, string?

372
00:23:24,571 --> 00:23:26,864
Me too, man. Me, too.

373
00:23:45,425 --> 00:23:49,804
- East side wasn't ready for us?
- That's what I'm saying.

374
00:23:57,270 --> 00:24:00,815
Yeah, I know all about baba jani
and his 24-hour turnover.

375
00:24:01,441 --> 00:24:03,901
It's a real pain in my ass, too.

376
00:24:03,985 --> 00:24:05,820
He's got a problem with the school kids.

377
00:24:05,903 --> 00:24:09,115
Every afternoon they go in there,
crowd him at the counter,

378
00:24:09,198 --> 00:24:11,117
boost all the car and gun magazines.

379
00:24:11,492 --> 00:24:15,788
That surveillance tape's so grainy
it's like watching buffalo in a snowstorm.

380
00:24:15,872 --> 00:24:18,499
But my insurance man, Bob,

381
00:24:18,875 --> 00:24:21,878
I got him to turn this camera here
right on baba's parking lot.

382
00:24:22,378 --> 00:24:26,049
Now, any time I have a real problem,
I just come to Bob and pull his tape.

383
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:29,594
I can get a copy of that for you
in the morning.

384
00:24:32,930 --> 00:24:35,850
Your partner there.

385
00:24:36,726 --> 00:24:38,561
Bit of an asshole.

386
00:24:40,063 --> 00:24:42,607
- For real?
- Yeah.

387
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:47,904
Good, good, good! That's it! Work!

388
00:24:49,697 --> 00:24:51,949
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Go to your right.

389
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:55,078
One, two, three!

390
00:25:14,097 --> 00:25:16,099
Yeah, right hand up.

391
00:25:25,358 --> 00:25:28,277
You know what this is? It's moral midgetry.

392
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:33,366
Turn the fucking world upside down and treat
these braindead corner yos like princelings.

393
00:25:33,783 --> 00:25:35,618
You see how clean the corners are?

394
00:25:35,785 --> 00:25:38,121
Street traffic is half what it was.

395
00:25:38,287 --> 00:25:40,707
Fuck that. It's wrong, and it's wrong.

396
00:25:40,998 --> 00:25:43,334
Because the other way
we were doing so well.

397
00:25:43,668 --> 00:25:47,714
Colvin's answer is what? Ride shotgun
for hoppers? Drown them in cash money?

398
00:25:47,797 --> 00:25:49,507
Colvin? He's always been good police.

399
00:25:49,590 --> 00:25:53,469
Then he's got to know what a heartbreaker
it is to suit up for this shit.

400
00:25:53,636 --> 00:25:55,346
He's got to suit up too, man.

401
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:58,307
Somebody should dime the brass
about this shit.

402
00:25:58,933 --> 00:26:01,394
- Or the sun papers.
- Let me ask you something.

403
00:26:01,936 --> 00:26:05,273
Anybody here getjammed up
and not have Colvin go to the wall for you?

404
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:09,610
The man is trying something. It may
be hard to stomach, but it's working.

405
00:26:09,694 --> 00:26:13,114
After 30 years,
he's earned the right to some elbow room.

406
00:26:13,197 --> 00:26:16,117
What the fuck.
This thing is on borrowed time, anyhow.

407
00:26:16,325 --> 00:26:19,245
And when we do decide
to jump on hamsterdams

408
00:26:19,328 --> 00:26:21,998
they're just gonna go back
to their regular corners, right?

409
00:26:22,081 --> 00:26:25,668
If we everjump out on it.
I don't know that we're gonna.

410
00:26:25,835 --> 00:26:29,881
All I'm saying is let's give the guy
the same backup he's always given us.

411
00:26:30,339 --> 00:26:32,467
That's all I'm saying.

412
00:26:36,679 --> 00:26:40,516
I swear, as soon as the sun comes up,
we grab that damn tape and go.

413
00:26:41,058 --> 00:26:43,060
This place makes me want to cry.

414
00:26:43,728 --> 00:26:46,355
I spent half my marriage
in rooms like this.

415
00:26:48,191 --> 00:26:49,692
How could you do it?

416
00:26:50,902 --> 00:26:52,236
What?

417
00:26:53,029 --> 00:26:56,824
- Go nonstop hound on your ex like that.
- It's easy.

418
00:26:57,074 --> 00:26:59,410
Just tell her I was on the road
working an extradition.

419
00:27:00,703 --> 00:27:02,121
Lots of extraditions.

420
00:27:03,039 --> 00:27:06,209
Brought back something like 500 fugitives
in a three-year period, I think.

421
00:27:07,043 --> 00:27:10,087
- That's not what I meant.
- Right.

422
00:27:16,594 --> 00:27:18,596
So, you're back in the house?

423
00:27:20,807 --> 00:27:22,975
Ate some shit and she took me back, yeah.

424
00:27:24,894 --> 00:27:27,313
I ain't sure I even
want to be back, though.

425
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:34,946
Extraditions, huh?

426
00:27:36,155 --> 00:27:39,492
- Cheryl would see right through that shit.
- No, it's easy.

427
00:27:40,785 --> 00:27:43,746
You keep your cell off,
make sure she can reach your partner.

428
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,916
Partner tells her, "kima's in court"
or whatever.

429
00:27:47,375 --> 00:27:51,254
Partner calls you, gives you the heads up, you
call her back later like, "hey, what's up?"

430
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:02,306
Ain't even got a quarter box
for the magic fingers.

431
00:28:04,851 --> 00:28:06,611
Maybe you don't need
a quarter box for that.

432
00:28:08,396 --> 00:28:09,605
For what?

433
00:28:10,690 --> 00:28:12,108
Magic fingers.

434
00:28:20,616 --> 00:28:21,951
You know me.

435
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:25,705
With a singer-songwriter
who's burnin' up the charts

436
00:28:25,788 --> 00:28:27,957
with a hit that he'll
perform for us tonight...

437
00:28:44,348 --> 00:28:47,018
- You hustling?
- Educating.

438
00:28:49,312 --> 00:28:51,814
Are you charging for it or tuition-free?

439
00:28:51,898 --> 00:28:55,234
Tuition will come back to him tenfold
in acquired wisdom.

440
00:28:55,318 --> 00:28:58,821
Besides, nothing in the world's
more expensive than "free."

441
00:28:58,905 --> 00:29:00,406
That's all she wrote.

442
00:29:01,490 --> 00:29:02,575
Let's double it.

443
00:29:02,658 --> 00:29:05,536
I don't like taking money
from a churchgoing man.

444
00:29:05,620 --> 00:29:07,914
- Triple it.
- Your break, Deacon.

445
00:29:13,252 --> 00:29:15,713
We need to talk
some more about hamsterdam.

446
00:29:15,796 --> 00:29:17,548
Look, I never said it was pretty.

447
00:29:17,632 --> 00:29:20,885
Pretty doesn't even come close
to the problem.

448
00:29:20,968 --> 00:29:22,720
We need to talk.

449
00:29:26,223 --> 00:29:28,184
I've got a comstat meeting.

450
00:29:28,851 --> 00:29:30,853
I'll drop by later on.

451
00:29:35,024 --> 00:29:38,110
- So we good with the permits?
- Yeah, this week, so far, so good.

452
00:29:38,527 --> 00:29:41,572
- All right.
- Look at you.

453
00:29:41,864 --> 00:29:44,575
- Who?
- Chunky coates.

454
00:29:44,659 --> 00:29:46,869
- Who's that?
- You don't know chunky?

455
00:29:47,036 --> 00:29:50,498
He's got the properties down the block
and over on paca street.

456
00:29:50,581 --> 00:29:55,795
He used to have an office so small you had
to leave the room to change your mind.

457
00:29:55,878 --> 00:29:59,340
Then two years ago he started running
with your man, Clay Davis.

458
00:30:01,425 --> 00:30:04,053
Look at you now, you big sassy bitch.

459
00:30:05,346 --> 00:30:07,431
- That better?
- Mm-hm.

460
00:30:08,391 --> 00:30:13,062
Hey, special agent fitzhugh,
if that is in fact your real name.

461
00:30:14,563 --> 00:30:17,066
FBI in on this?

462
00:30:17,191 --> 00:30:20,528
I am only loved for my toys.
Lester called and I delivered.

463
00:30:20,736 --> 00:30:22,613
You got the tape?

464
00:30:23,489 --> 00:30:27,994
Date of 10/10/04.15:04 hours, 30 seconds...

465
00:30:28,077 --> 00:30:29,745
By the register tape.

466
00:30:35,251 --> 00:30:37,253
Mama barksdale?

467
00:30:39,088 --> 00:30:40,506
D'Angelo's mother.

468
00:30:40,631 --> 00:30:44,343
She cold-called mcnulty
about her son on the jailhouse hanging.

469
00:30:44,427 --> 00:30:46,929
She's calling us on that weak shit?

470
00:30:47,054 --> 00:30:50,683
Is this, er, Brianna? Right.

471
00:30:50,766 --> 00:30:53,853
You called about your son.
I'm returning that message.

472
00:30:54,854 --> 00:30:55,855
Uh-oh.

473
00:30:57,898 --> 00:30:59,108
Nothing there.

